gomodel:SYNGO_2852  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Fig.2: \"cAMP-mediated potentiation of transmitter release is impaired in Epac2-/- mice\"\n\nFig.3: \"MF-LTP is impaired in Epac2-/- mice. A, Time course of MF-LTP in Epac2+/+ mice\"\n\nFig.7: \"Functional estimates of the total number of synaptic vesicles available for release in Epac2+/+ and Epac2-/- MF boutons\"\n- \" these data indicate that N, the number of readily releasable vesicles, is significantly reduced in Epac2-/- mice... This study proposes a novel mechanism for enhancement of transmitter release at MF synapses involving a noncanonical cAMP target and uncovers a novel role for Epac2 as a synapse-specific regulator of the RRP of vesicles.\"\n\nNote: LTP in the MF->CA3 synapse is known to be mediated by a presynaptic mechanism.. Experimental description: - \"Epac2-/- mice were obtained (from S. Seino, Kobe University, J...\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0593-3443" ;
        dc:date           "2018-03-09" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_2852" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

